The spectra of 29Si MAS-NMR are presented in Fig. 6
                         for all the hardened pastes and raw GGBFSs with the deconvoluted curves (see Table 4
                        ). The deconvolution of 29Si MAS-NMR spectra was performed using the DMFit software package [48] referring to earlier studies [2,3,10,36–38,49,50]; the Gaussian function was used for fitting the spectra of the original GGBFS and unreacted GGBFS; however, the Lorentzian was used for the other deconvoluted curves of the Q1 and Q2 peaks [36]; following Bernal et al. [37], we also assumed that the original positions and shapes of the unreacted GGBFS spectra would not be changed after CaO-activation, but only the intensities would be reduced during curing. Thus, in the deconvolution process, to assign residual GGBFS (i.e., Q0), the original location and shape of spectrum curve of raw GGBFS were used, and only the intensity of the curve was adjusted; in particular, FWHH (full width at half height) of each deconvoluted curve for Q1 and Q2 was limited to below 10 ppm in deconvolution after referring to Bernal et al. [37].
